# DNS Exfiltration Detection

## Detection Criteria
1. DNS queries with abnormally long subdomains (>50 chars)
2. High label count (>5 dots in domain)
3. High Shannon entropy (>4.0) indicating random/encoded data
4. Burst of queries (>20 in 5 minutes)

## False Positives
- CDN services (akamai, cloudfront) - whitelist known patterns
- Certificate transparency logs
- Legitimate base64-encoded tracking parameters

## Tuning
```kql
| where Name !contains "akamaitechnologies.com"
| where Name !contains "cloudfront.net"
```
